~ wake_up
Tux: Psst... Nova... wake up.
Tux: You slept through the entire Systems class again.
Tux: I had to drag your session out before the compiler ate your homework.
Tux: Name is Tux. I am your guide, debugger, and occasional voice of reason.
Tux: First check: can you move with WASD?
=> END

~ movement_success
Tux: Nice. Movement online.
Tux: Good, because standing still in this world is how bugs win.
Tux: Next, walk up to the glowing marker and press E to interact.
=> END

~ interact_prompt
Tux: Interaction is your handshake with the world.
Tux: Get close to the marker, then press E.
=> END

~ interact_success
Tux: Perfect. Input pipeline confirmed.
=> END

~ hud_unlock
Tux: Time to unlock your HUD.
Tux: Bottom-right panel has your two anchors:
Tux: TUX icon is for quick tutorial tips and mission beats.
Tux: TERMINAL icon is for your terminal.
Tux: To access the skill shop, open TERMINAL and run: shop.
Tux: We survive Linuxia by reading the system, not guessing.
=> END

~ terminal_objective
Tux: Terminal check. Open TERMINAL and run these commands:
Tux: 1) pwd
Tux: 2) ls
Tux: 3) cat <file-name>  (example: cat lost-file)
Tux: I will wait here until all three are done.
=> END

~ terminal_complete
Tux: Clean execution.
Tux: You now have the basics: orientation, listing, and combining file contents.
=> END

~ linuxia_ready
Tux: Final question, Nova. Ready to enter Linuxia?
- What is Linuxia?
	=> linuxia_explain
- I am ready. Let's go.
	=> linuxia_yes
- Not yet, give me one more minute.
	=> linuxia_no

~ linuxia_explain
Tux: Linuxia is the live system beyond this safe zone.
Tux: Every command has consequences there.
Tux: Read output, think before acting, and you will be fine.
- Okay. I am ready.
	=> linuxia_yes
- I still need a moment.
	=> linuxia_no

~ linuxia_yes
Tux: Good. Confidence plus caution. That is how admins are made.
=> END

~ linuxia_no
Tux: Fair. A careful operator beats a reckless hero.
Tux: Ping me from the TUX panel when you are ready.
=> END

~ linuxia_arrival_intro
Tux: Welcome to Linuxia proper, Nova. I am with you from here on.
Tux: Think of me as your guide while you map this system and its people.
Tux: Before charging into deeper zones, talk to the NPCs in this hamlet first.
Tux: They will teach you the tools, risks, and routes you need to survive.
Tux: Ask questions, read carefully, and we will move as a team.
=> END
